Content:
but the previous website[0] was also minimal and yet (IMVHO) a lot more effective (and a lot easier to read)[1].<p>[0] <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20151103063328/http://iolanguage.org/" rel="nofollow">https://web.archive.org/web/20151103063328/http://iolanguage...</a><p>[1] EDIT: I am slightly astygmatic, so for me thin white lines on black BG are basically just horizontal fuzzyness. To be constructive: white on black is generally less readable, but it can be somewhat compensated by adding more leading and thicker lines, so i.e. in /about adding this to .text<p><pre><code>    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: normal;
    letter-spacing: .015rem;
</code></pre>
makes it a lot easier to read.
